results.name: a(n) is least prime p such that 7 is the n-th term in the Euclid-Mullin sequence starting at p, or 0 if no such prime p exists.
comment: The sequence is not monotonic. Compare to A093882.
Next term exceeds 50000. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jan 12 2012
example: a(5)=11 because p=7 first arises in EM at position 5, which is initiated with 11: {11,2,23,3,7,10627,433}; see A051309.
